    <item>
      <title>Noob - Walkthrough</title>
      <link>https://nvru.github.io/walkthrough/hmv/noob/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 24 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://nvru.github.io/walkthrough/hmv/noob/</guid>
      
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attacker IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.2&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target Machine IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.37&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The objective was to enumerate the target, identify exposed services, gain initial access by recovering an exposed SSH private key from the web server, and escalate privileges by abusing the web server&amp;rsquo;s ability to access files through symbolic links.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://nvru.github.io/images/hmv/noob/vm.png&#34; alt=&#34;Machine information&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;port-scanning&#34;&gt;Port Scanning&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;rustscan&#34;&gt;RustScan&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rustscan -a 10.10.10.37 -- -sC -sV -A -oA nmap/rust
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;results&#34;&gt;Results&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PORT      STATE SERVICE VERSION
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;22/tcp    open  ssh     OpenSSH 7.9p1 Debian 10+deb10u2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;65530/tcp open  http    Golang net/http server
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Only two services were exposed:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Observer - Walkthrough</title>
      <link>https://nvru.github.io/walkthrough/hmv/observer/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://nvru.github.io/walkthrough/hmv/observer/</guid>
      
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attacker IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.2&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target Machine IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.36&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The objective was to enumerate the target, identify exposed services, gain initial access through the vulnerable HTTP file observer service, and escalate privileges through exposed credentials and sudo permissions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://nvru.github.io/images/hmv/observer/vm.png&#34; alt=&#34;Machine information&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;port-scanning&#34;&gt;Port Scanning&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;rustscan&#34;&gt;RustScan&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rustscan -a 10.10.10.36 -- -sC -sV -A -oA nmap/rust
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;results&#34;&gt;Results&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PORT     STATE SERVICE REASON  VERSION
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;22/tcp   open  ssh     syn-ack OpenSSH 9.2p1 Debian 2 (protocol 2.0)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;3333/tcp open  http    syn-ack Golang net/http server
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The scan revealed two exposed services:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Who Wants to Be King? 1 - Walkthrough</title>
      <link>https://nvru.github.io/walkthrough/vulnhub/who_wants_to_be_king1/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 20 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://nvru.github.io/walkthrough/vulnhub/who_wants_to_be_king1/</guid>
      
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attacker IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.245.58.142&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target Machine IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.245.58.27&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The objective was to enumerate the target, identify exposed services, gain initial access by recovering credentials from an exposed binary, and escalate privileges by discovering the root password through user artifacts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://nvru.github.io/images/vulnhub/who_wants_to_be_king1/logscreen.png&#34; alt=&#34;Machine information&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;enumeration&#34;&gt;Enumeration&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;port-scanning&#34;&gt;Port Scanning&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;rustscan&#34;&gt;RustScan&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rustscan -a 10.245.58.27
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Output:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Open 10.245.58.27:22
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Open 10.245.58.27:80
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4 id=&#34;nmap&#34;&gt;Nmap&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo nmap -sSCV 10.245.58.27 -A -p22,80 -oN nmap/ports
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Results:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PORT   STATE SERVICE VERSION
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;22/tcp open  ssh     OpenSSH 8.2p1 Ubuntu 4
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;80/tcp open  http    Apache httpd 2.4.41
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;http-title: Index of /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;http-server-header: Apache/2.4.41 (Ubuntu)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Index of /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;31K  skeylogger
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Only SSH and HTTP were exposed. The web server had directory listing enabled and exposed a single file named &lt;strong&gt;skeylogger&lt;/strong&gt;, making it the obvious target for further enumeration.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>CCTV - Walkthrough</title>
      <link>https://nvru.github.io/walkthrough/htb/cctv/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 12 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://nvru.github.io/walkthrough/htb/cctv/</guid>
      
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attacker IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.14.24&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target Machine IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.129.50.93&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The objective was to enumerate the target, identify exposed services, gain initial access through a SQL injection vulnerability in ZoneMinder, and escalate privileges by exploiting a vulnerable MotionEye instance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://nvru.github.io/images/htb/cctv/vm.png&#34; alt=&#34;Machine information&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;port-scanning&#34;&gt;Port Scanning&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;rustscan&#34;&gt;RustScan&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rustscan -a 10.129.50.93 -- -A -oA nmap/rust
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;results&#34;&gt;Results&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PORT   STATE SERVICE VERSION
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;22/tcp open  ssh     OpenSSH 9.6p1 Ubuntu 3ubuntu13.14 (Ubuntu Linux; protocol 2.0)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;80/tcp open  http    Apache httpd 2.4.58
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;|_http-title: Did not follow redirect to http://cctv.htb/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Only a few services were exposed externally, making web enumeration the next logical step.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Pingme - Walkthrough</title>
      <link>https://nvru.github.io/walkthrough/hmv/pingme/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 11 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://nvru.github.io/walkthrough/hmv/pingme/</guid>
      
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attacker IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.2&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target Machine IP:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.21&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The objective was to enumerate the target, identify exposed services, gain initial access by recovering credentials leaked through ICMP packets, and escalate privileges by abusing a root-owned script that allowed arbitrary file transmission over ICMP.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://nvru.github.io/images/hmv/pingme/vm.png&#34; alt=&#34;Machine information&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;port-scanning&#34;&gt;Port Scanning&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;rustscan&#34;&gt;RustScan&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rustscan -a 10.10.10.21 -- -sC -sV -A -oA nmap/rust
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4 id=&#34;results&#34;&gt;Results&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;PORT   STATE SERVICE VERSION
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;22/tcp open  ssh     OpenSSH 8.4p1 Debian 5 (protocol 2.0)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;80/tcp open  http    nginx 1.18.0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Service Info: OS: Linux
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Only SSH and HTTP were exposed. Since SSH did not provide an entry point yet, I started with web enumeration.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
